  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Nutrition for child survival in Niger: scaling up and improving the quality of management of acute malnutrition among children under five</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">There is a continuum of care between treatment of moderate and severe acute malnutrition. Treatment of cases of Moderate malnutrition is supported by WFP while support for treatment of severe acute malnutrition is supported by UNICEF. Despite this clear task distribution, UNICEF and WFP worked together in the sense that cases of severe acute malnutrition identify in treatment site for moderate malnutrition (CRENAM) are sent to treatment site of severe acute malnutrition (CRENI/CRENAS) and vice versa.</narrative>
  </description>
